A warm, sunlit Singapore classroom scene in Studio Ghibli style, showing a cascading visual metaphor of knowledge flowing downward like gentle streams of light. At the top, an ornate government building with traditional Asian architectural elements releases glowing particles that drift down through floating translucent layers, each layer representing a different level of the education system. Young students in white uniforms sit at wooden desks below, their faces illuminated with wonder as they catch these luminous knowledge particles in their hands. Lush tropical plants peek through open windows, and a gentle breeze rustles papers on desks. The color palette features soft pastels with warm golden afternoon light, characteristic Ghibli cloud formations visible through the windows, and delicate attention to small details like pencils, notebooks, and a curious gecko on the wall. The composition emphasizes the vertical flow from institution to individual student, creating a sense of structured yet nurturing educational guidance.
